SEC Notice of Effectiveness

Source: R/effectiveness.R
effectiveness.Rd

Returns the current Noice of Effectiveness from the most recently completed business day from here

effectiveness()

Value

a data.frame with each row as a submission with the following columns:

registration_number

file_href

registrant

registrant_href

filing_date

effective_date

division

type

Details

You can also see the same filings going further back by using `latest_filings()` specifying the type = "EFFECT"

Examples
